ize before the join operation.\n2. **Apply FILTER_MERGE**: Combine filter conditions where possible to simplify the query.\n3. **Apply PROJECT_FILTER_TRANSPOSE**: Push projections past filters to reduce the data processed early.\n\n### Optimized Query:\nAfter applying the selected rules, the query structure remains largely the same, but with improved efficiency due to reduced data processing in joins and filters.\n\n```python\n[\n    "FILTER_INTO_JOIN",\n    "FILTER_MERGE",\n    "PROJECT_FILTER_TRANSPOSE"\n]\n```\n\nThese steps should help in optimizing the query by reducing the amount of data processed in joins and filters, leading to better performance.', 'time': 5.517947673797607}
